XrBK3yw==\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Wmje4I1UnJmcdF0WxeCjoyIW|fc_0ad52cba65e839250169fa24d135e8819c823e30ff36bc4eb3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-main-kts/2.3.21/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_main_kts/ClassRealmTest.kt", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_jetbrains_kotlin.kotlin_main_kts\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\nimport org.jetbrains.kotlin.org.codehaus.plexus.classworlds.ClassWorld\nimport org.jetbrains.kotlin.org.codehaus.plexus.classworlds.realm.ClassRealm\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir\nimport java.net.URL\nimport java.nio.file.Files\nimport java.nio.file.Path\nimport java.util.Collections\nimport java.util.Enumeration\n\npublic class ClassRealmTest {\n    @Test\n    fun selfLookupsUseUrlClassLoaderMethods(): Unit {\n        val realm = TestClassRealm(\"self\")\n        val missingClassName = \"example.DoesNotExist\"\n        val missingResourceName = \"example/missing-resource.txt\"\n\n        assertThat(loadClassFromSelfAllowingNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(realm, missingClassName)).isNull()\n        assertThat(realm.getResource(missingResourceName)).isNull()\n        assertThat(Collections.list(realm.getResources(missingResourceName))).isEmpty()\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun importLookupsDelegateToImportClassLoader(@TempDir tempDir: Path): Unit {\n        val resourceName = \"import-resource.txt\"\n        val resourceUrl = createResource(tempDir, resourceName)\n        val importClassLoader = RecordingClassLoader(mapOf(resourceName to listOf(resourceUrl)))\n        val realm = TestClassRealm(\"import\", importClassLoader = importClassLoader)\n\n        assertThat(realm.loadClassFromImport(String::class.java.name)).isSameAs(String::class.java)\n        assertThat(realm.loadResourceFromImport(resourceName)).isEqualTo(resourceUrl)\n        assertThat(Collections.list(realm.loadResourcesFromImport(resourceName))).containsExactly(resourceUrl)\n\n        assertThat(importClassLoader.loadedClassNames).containsExactly(String::class.java.name)\n        assertThat(importClassLoader.resourceNames).contains(resourceName)\n        assertThat(importClassLoader.resourceEnumerationNames).contains(resourceName)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun parentLookupsDelegateToParentClassLoader(@TempDir tempDir: Path): Unit {\n        val resourceName = \"parent-resource.txt\"\n        val resourceUrl = createResource(tempDir, resourceName)\n        val parentClassLoader = RecordingClassLoader(mapOf(resourceName to listOf(resourceUrl)))\n        val realm = TestClassRealm(\"parent\", parentClassLoaderOverride = parentClassLoader)\n\n        assertThat(realm.loadClassFromParent(String::class.java.name)).isSameAs(String::class.java)\n        assertThat(realm.loadResourceFromParent(resourceName)).isEqualTo(resourceUrl)\n        assertThat(Collections.list(realm.loadResourcesFromParent(resourceName))).containsExactly(resourceUrl)\n\n        assertThat(parentClassLoader.loadedClassNames).containsExactly(String::class.java.name)\n        assertThat(parentClassLoader.resourceNames).contains(resourceName)\n        assertThat(parentClassLoader.resourceEnumerationNames).contains(resourceName)\n    }\n\n    private fun createResource(tempDir: Path, resourceName: String): URL {\n        val resourceFile = Files.writeString(tempDir.resolve(resourceName), resourceName)\n        return resourceFile.toUri().toURL()\n    }\n\n    private fun loadClassFromSelfAllowingNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(realm: ClassRealm, className: String): Class<*>? {\n        return try {\n            realm.loadClassFromSelf(className)\n        } catch (error: Error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error\n            }\n            null\n        }\n    }\n\n    public class TestClassRealm(\n        id: String,\n        private val importClassLoader: ClassLoader? = null,\n        private val parentClassLoaderOverride: ClassLoader? = null,\n    ) : ClassRealm(ClassWorld(), id, null) {\n        override fun getImportClassLoader(name: String): ClassLoader? = importClassLoader\n\n        override fun getParentClassLoader(): ClassLoader? = parentClassLoaderOverride\n    }\n\n    public class RecordingClassLoader(\n        private val resourcesByName: Map<String, List<URL>>,\n    ) : ClassLoader(null) {\n        public val loadedClassNames: MutableList<String> = mutableListOf()\n        public val resourceNames: MutableList<String> = mutableListOf()\n        public val resourceEnumerationNames: MutableList<String> = mutableListOf()\n\n        override fun loadClass(name: String): Class<*> {\n            loadedClassNames.add(name)\n            if (name == String::class.java.name) {\n                return String::class.java\n            }\n            throw ClassNotFoundException(name)\n        }\n\n        override fun getResource(name: String): URL? {\n            resourceNames.add(name)\n            return resourcesByName[name]?.firstOrNull()\n        }\n\n        override fun getResources(name: String): Enumeration<URL> {\n            resourceEnumerationNames.add(name)\n            return Collections.enumeration(resourcesByName[name].orEmpty())\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1875, "output": 1357, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42144, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778001101205, "responseId": "resp_0ad52cba65e839250169fa24cdf0d8819cb870e7a2849cf182"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolC